Creating a simple "Skyrim clone" in a single HTML file is quite a challenge, as Skyrim is a complex game with 3D graphics, AI, and a vast world. However, I can provide you with a very basic web app that mimics some elements of an RPG game using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This will be a simple text-based adventure game that you can expand upon.

Here's a basic example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Skyrim Clone</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: #ecf0f1;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #game {
            border: 1px solid #ecf0f1;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #34495e;
        }
        #output {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            height: 150px;
            overflow-y: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ecf0f1;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #2c3e50;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 5px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #e74c3c;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #c0392b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="game">
        <h1>Simple Skyrim Clone</h1>
        <div id="output"></div>
        <button onclick="explore()">Explore</button>
        <button onclick="rest()">Rest</button>
        <button onclick="fight()">Fight</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        let health = 100;
        let output = document.getElementById('output');

        function updateOutput(message) {
            output.innerHTML += message + '<br>';
            output.scrollTop = output.scrollHeight; // Auto-scroll to the bottom
        }

        function explore() {
            const events = [
                "You found a treasure chest!",
                "You encountered a wild animal!",
                "You discovered a hidden cave!",
                "You met a friendly NPC who offers you a quest."
            ];
            const randomEvent = events[Math.floor(Math.random() * events.length)];
            updateOutput(randomEvent);
        }

        function rest() {
            health = Math.min(100, health + 20);
            updateOutput("You rest and regain health. Current health: " + health);
        }

        function fight() {
            const damage = Math.floor(Math.random() * 30);
            health -= damage;
            if (health <= 0) {
                health = 0;
                updateOutput("You have been defeated! Game Over.");
                disableButtons();
            } else {
                updateOutput("You fought bravely and took " + damage + " damage. Current health: " + health);
            }
        }

        function disableButtons() {
            const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('button');
            buttons.forEach(button => button.disabled = true);
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `skyrim_clone.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### Features:
- **Explore**: Random events occur when you click this button.
- **Rest**: Regain health.
- **Fight**: Simulate taking damage.

This is a very basic text-based RPG. You can expand it by adding more features, such as inventory management, more complex combat mechanics, quests, and a more detailed storyline.

